main event: Several witnesses observed an unidentified flying object near Cleveland, Ohio on November 9, 1965.
interesting points: The object was estimated to be flying at speeds between 5200-7300 MPH., The object was described as Zeppelin-shaped and bluish in color., The sighting lasted approximately 5 to 10 minutes, during which the object hovered and then appeared to accelerate rapidly., The witness stated that the object was clearly not an aircraft or weather balloon., There was no photographic evidence obtained for the sighting.
witness description: The witness mentioned being an earnest observer, not seeking publicity.
